==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Roost
<hw>Roost</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>hr⟦omac⟧st</ets>; akin to
OD. <ets>roest</ets> roost, <ets>roesten</ets> to roost, and probably to
E. <ets>roof</ets>. Cf. <er>Roof</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The pole
or other support on which fowls rest at night; a perch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He clapped his wings upon his <qex>roost</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collection of fowls roosting together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>At roost</b></col>, <cd>on a perch or roost; hence,
retired to rest.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roost</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Roost
<hw>Roost</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Roosted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Roosting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To sit, rest, or
sleep, as fowls on a pole, limb of a tree, etc.; to perch.</def>
<rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.; To lodge; to rest; to sleep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, let me where thy roof my soul hath hid,⟦br⟧
O, let me <qex>roost</qex> and nestle there.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roostcock</ent>⟦br⟧
